<subSubSection lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="211" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1900,2033]" lastBlockId="24.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="211" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1972,1997]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Males of this species differ from other congeners except 
<taxonomicName authority="Menge, 1872" authorityName="Menge" authorityYear="1872" box="[969,1359,1972,1997]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerea">
<emphasis box="[969,1185,1972,1997]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Berlandina cinerea</emphasis>
(Menge, 
<number box="[1293,1350,1973,1997]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="1872.0">1872</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the large tibial apophysis (
<number box="[407,417,2009,2033]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[427,443,2009,2033]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="2.0">2</number>
of cymbial length), the long and thin embolus starting at 
<number box="[1090,1104,2009,2033]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="8.0">8</number>
o’clock with a strongly (
<number box="[1387,1418,2009,2033]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="90.0">90</number>
°) bent tip. From 
<taxonomicName box="[317,432,153,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerea">
<emphasis box="[317,432,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="211">B. cinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by the thin and bent embolus. The female of 
<taxonomicName box="[1044,1217,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nabozhenkoi">
<emphasis box="[1044,1217,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="211">B. nabozhenkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,288,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yakovlevi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[151,288,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="211">B. yakovlevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[294,358,188,213]" pageId="24" pageNumber="211" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[294,358,188,213]" pageId="24" pageNumber="211">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from which it can be distinguished by the thinner septum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="211" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="24" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,223,248]" pageId="24" pageNumber="211">Comments</emphasis>
. The species is well described in above mentioned papers. We were not able to study and to illustrate the female of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
